.TH "dma_buf_pin" 9 "dma_buf_pin" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dma_buf_pin \- Lock down the DMA-buf
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dma_buf_pin
.BI "(struct dma_buf_attachment *attach "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "attach" 12
[in]    attachment which should be pinned
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Only dynamic importers (who set up \fIattach\fP with \fBdma_buf_dynamic_attach\fP) may
call this, and only for limited use cases like scanout and not for temporary
pin operations. It is not permitted to allow userspace to pin arbitrary
amounts of buffers through this interface.

Buffers must be unpinned by calling \fBdma_buf_unpin\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative error code on failure.
